article.headline: St. Bonaventure 79, Presbyterian 72
article.story: ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. (AP) -- Michael Lee scored 13 of his 21 points in the second half and Tyler Relph also finished with 21, shooting 6-for-7 on 3-pointers, as St. Bonaventure beat Presbyterian 79-72 on Sunday. Zarryon Fereti scored 18 points and center D'Lancy Carter added 10 rebounds for the Bonnies (3-2), whose only loss during the three-day Basketball Travelers Invitational was to host New Mexico. The Blue Hose (0-4) led 55-50 after Walt Allen's 3-pointer near the 12-minute mark but Lee made three baskets, including a steal and dunk, as St. Bonaventure rallied with an 11-4 run and went ahead for good. The Bonnies shot 9-of-11 at the free throw line in the final 1:34 to pull away. Pat Kiscaden scored 15 points, hitting 5-of-8 on 3-point tries for Presbyterian, a 1,200-student school in Clinton, S.C., that is playing its first Division I season. Bryan Bostic scored 12 while Pierre Miller and Travis Sligh each had 10.
